x(t),u(t))$ of the closed-loop system converges to $(\\Xi(u_r),u_r)$, then the\ntracking error $r-y$ tends to zero. The compact set $X_T$ can be made larger by\nchoosing a larger parameter $T>0$, resulting in smaller $k$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Oct 2016 14:39:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Jan 2021 11:11:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-14"}
